  "text": "The Prometheus server repository enforces metric naming conventions through validation functions imported from the prometheus/common/model package (model.UTF8Validation and model.LegacyValidation). These validation schemes provide methods IsValidMetricName() and IsValidLabelName() that are used throughout the codebase to enforce naming conventions. The enforcement occurs at multiple levels: (1) Label validation in model/labels/labels_common.go through the IsValid() method and Validate() function which validate metric names and label names against the configured validation scheme; (2) Relabeling configuration validation in model/relabel/relabel.go in the Validate() method which ensures target labels conform to naming conventions; (3) Recording and alerting rule validation in model/rulefmt/rulefmt.go in RuleGroups.Validate() and Rule.Validate() methods which validate metric names and label names for recording rules; (4) Protobuf format parsing in model/textparse/protobufparse.go in the Next() method which validates metric names using IsValidMetricName() and help text format using utf8.ValidString(); (5) Global configuration validation in config/config.go which validates external labels; (6) Remote storage codec validation in storage/remote/codec.go through validateLabelsAndMetricName() function; (7) Protobuf decoder validation in prompb/io/prometheus/client/decoder.go which validates label names during metric label parsing; (8) PromQL engine validation in promql/engine.go for COUNT_VALUES operation; (9) PromQL function validation in promql/functions.go for label_replace() and label_join() functions; (10) PromQL parser validation in promql/parser/generated_parser.y.go and promql/parser/printer.go; (11) Web API validation in web/api/v1/api.go; (12) Validation scheme checking utility in util/namevalidationutil/namevalidationutil.go. The validation enforces three key conventions: metric name validation (snake_case with alphanumeric and underscores), label name validation (similar to metric names but distinct rules), and help text validation (UTF-8 format compliance)."
}

